dcterms:description: The Ubuntu V2 corpus consists of conversations extracted from Ubuntu chat logs, where people seek technical support for various Ubuntu-related problems from the community.
dcterms:title: Ubuntu V2

dcterms:description: The Advising dataset from DSTC7 subtask 1 contains dialogues in which university students seek advice on classes to take. The dataset was built upon expanding 815 original conversations by paraphrasing.
dcterms:title: Advising DSTC7

dcterms:description: The Ubuntu DSTC7 dataset is similar to the Ubuntu V2 corpus, but it was further disentangled and annotated from the original chat logs data. The goal is to select the most appropriate response from 100 candidates.
dcterms:title: Ubuntu DSTC7

dcterms:description: The Taskmaster dataset consists of written dialogues in the movie ticketing domain. The dialogues are split into train/dev/test sets, treating each system turn and its corresponding dialogue context as a positive pair.
dcterms:title: Taskmaster
